One of Colombia’s most successful series, the musical telenovela ‘The Queen of Flow’ has returned for a second season. According to a statement by StarTimes, the second season of the series began airing  a week back.   Miracle Nduka breaks new grounds     SiSobola promises to always put smiles on people’s faces     Season 3 of MTV Base Cypher premieres   The Queen of Flow gained a cult following across many countries.   The pay-TV platform announced that season two will start airing daily at 8:30 pm on the ST Novela E Plus channel. Queen of Flow follows the story of a Colombian teenager Yeimy (Carolina Ramirez), who is set up by a local drug trafficker and finds herself sentenced to 25 years in prison. She returns home 17 years later to exact revenge on those who killed her family. The many twists and turns in this tale of love, revenge, and redemption are backed by the show’s soundtrack of reggaeton music performed by the cast.